The recent escalation in incidents of mob justice and stock theft across the province urged Provincial Police Commissioner Nneke Ledwaba and CPF chairpersons attached to police stations in Limpopo to engage in a meeting where prevention strategies were discussed in the city on Friday. Provincial Police Spokesperson Moatshe Ngoepe said the purpose of the session was to develop more community based crime prevention strategies and integrated solving techniques in terms of community concerns and complaints. Ledwaba has during the session also encouraged all the CPF structures to work closely with Police management at all levels in order to win the fight against crime and to address all concerns and complaints by communities, the business fraternity and farming communities, Ngoepe said. Among the attendees of the meeting were members of the Provincial Police Board and Provincial Head of Crime Prevention Sam Mokgonyana. The outcome of the meeting was not yet known at the time of going to print. Story: RC Myburgh &gt;&gt;rc.observer@gmail.com